parameters:
Royal Court Official Emoni: I would like to express my
gratitude to all of you for being able to come to the top
floor.

Royal Court Official Emoni: I have business beyond this
door, in the depths of the Betrayal Tower.
Clea: Is there something special there?

Royal Court Official Emoni: There is a switch here... Do you
understand its meaning?
Clea: I see, only one person can go to the very back.

Clea: We should each have our own reasons for being here.
How about we decide who goes to the very back through a fair
and square victory?

Royal Court Official Emoni: I might purposely lose and trap
you inside, you know?

Clea: I have a feeling... that you wouldn't do something
like that.

Clea: Besides, even if that were to happen, my companions
will definitely find a way to help me.

Royal Court Official Emoni: I trust you... I'm envious...
No, as you wish, I will let you fight!

Clea: I apologize for the change in the conditions of the
battle, but we would like to investigate the back.

Royal Court Official Emoni (Should I use [that grimoire]
here... but if I do, then they will... ugh... that's... )

Royal Court Official Emoni (I can't... engage in a serious
life-or-death battle... absolutely...)

Priestess Sophia: So this is the Tower of Betrayal, huh?
We've been completely deceived.

Mage Relm: I'm not good at all! A tower that disappoints
expectations is the worst kind of joke!

Royal Court Official Emoni: There really is nothing... I...
what on earth... all my efforts... ah...

Priestess Sophia: If it means becoming an enemy of Lex-
sama, who is as close to black as possible... then here...

Clea: Let's stop, Sophia-san. There was hostility, but there
was no intent to kill.

Clea: I think Prince Lex would dislike getting his hands
dirty with blood more than anyone else, don't you think?
Clea: Let's take them down to the bottom.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
Royal Court Official Emoni: Haa... haa...

Royal Court Official Emoni: I'm relieved. Everyone is just
unconscious... It's okay... I didn't kill anyone...

Royal Court Official Emoni: Why, why, why is this
happening!?

Royal Court Official Emoni: There's nothing... Why don't I
have the 【Staff of Dilark】!?

Royal Court Official Emoni: Wait a minute!? It's cowardly to
lock us up!

Royal Court Official Emoni: I can't break it with my
power... I don't know what's happening over there.

Royal Court Official Emoni: ...I suppose we can consider
this an emergency situation.

Royal Court Official Emoni: Evil demon Blarl of the Demon
Realm... Follow my orders and create monsters to destroy the
door!

Royal Court Official Emoni: Ngh... My life force is being
drained... *panting*... But it's better than being trapped
and dying.

Royal Court Official Emoni: Now, destroy the door! Obey the
orders of the esteemed Emoni-sama!

Royal Court Official Emoni: Hurry up! We need to report to
Lady Caron immediately!

Royal Court Official Emoni: Eh, wait, stay away, it's a
wall! I, stop, stop it, I don't like it, stop!
Would you like to skip the adult scene?

Do you want to restart from the battle? If you choose No, it
will result in a game over.
Will you touch the shrine of the foresight demon, Ipound?
Clea (Let's prepare first and then do it.)

Mage Relm: This... seems to be a shrine dedicated to the
demon Ipound.

Priestess Sophia: It's a demon that is said to have the
ability of foresight, and there is a somewhat silly episode
associated with it.
Thief Nora: What kind of story is it?

Priestess Sophia: It is said that the demon, Ipound, had the
ability to foresee the future and that there is a story
where it overestimated its own abilities and went to defeat
the hero, only to see its own demise and be defeated.

Mage Relm: Now that we know about the existence of the hero,
it's scary how it doesn't sound like a joke anymore...
Clea: It seems like the other party is ready.
Thief Nora: Ahh, I was scared... I'm glad everyone is safe.

Thief Nora: There's something beautiful that looks like a
jewel! Could this be the heart of the demon Ipound that
Elero was talking about?

Clea: Indeed, it looks like a beautiful jewel. Let's hand it
over to Elero-san for confirmation.
